#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:1
msgid "Comments"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:3
msgid "Follow RFC 1574 summary line conventions (`rfc1574-summary`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:5
msgid ""
"The first line of a doc comment should be concise and one sentence. Its "
"grammatical form depends on what the item is:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:8
msgid ""
"**Functions and methods** — third-person singular present indicative verb "
"(\"Returns\", \"Creates\", \"Acquires\"), describing the action performed."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:10
msgid ""
"**Types (structs, enums, traits, type aliases), modules, and fields** — a "
"noun phrase naming the thing, not describing an action. This matches the "
"Rust standard library convention (e.g., `Vec` is \"A contiguous growable "
"array type\")."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:16
msgid "/// Returns the mapping's start address.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:20
msgid ""
"/// A policy for how [`FsPath::from_fd_at`] treats an empty `path_str`.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:22
#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:25
msgid "/* ... */"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:23
msgid "/// A guard that releases a [`SpinLock`] when dropped.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:28
msgid "End sentence comments with punctuation (`comment-punctuation`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:30
msgid ""
"If a comment line is a full sentence, end it with proper punctuation. This "
"improves readability in dense code and avoids fragmented prose."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:36
msgid ""
"// Good — complete sentence with punctuation.\n"
"// SAFETY: The pointer is derived from a live allocation.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:38
msgid ""
"// Bad — complete sentence without punctuation\n"
"// SAFETY: The pointer is derived from a live allocation\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:43
msgid "Wrap identifiers in backticks (`backtick-identifiers`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:45
msgid ""
"Type names, method names, and code identifiers in doc comments should be "
"wrapped in backticks for rustdoc rendering. When referring to types, prefer "
"rustdoc links (`[TypeName]`) where possible."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:52
msgid ""
"/// Acquires the [`SpinLock`] and returns a guard\n"
"/// that releases the lock on [`Drop`].\n"
"///\n"
"/// Callers must not call `acquire` while holding\n"
"/// a [`RwMutex`] to avoid deadlock.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:60
msgid ""
"Do not disclose implementation details in doc comments (`no-impl-in-docs`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:62
msgid ""
"Doc comments should describe _what_ the API does and _how to use it_, not "
"_how it is implemented internally_."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:67
msgid ""
"// Good — behavior-oriented\n"
"/// Returns the number of active connections.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-maintainability/rust-specific/comments.md:69
msgid ""
"// Bad — leaks implementation details\n"
"/// Returns the length of the internal `HashMap`\n"
"/// that tracks connections by socket address.\n"
msgstr ""
